WEBVTT

00:00:35.536 --> 00:00:38.038
(upbeat music)

00:02:17.604 --> 00:02:20.307
(dramatic music)

00:02:22.776 --> 00:02:25.913
(Nezumi gasps)

00:02:25.946 --> 00:02:28.015
Get him! Don't
let, Nezumi escape.

00:02:28.048 --> 00:02:30.684
This time we'll
catch him in the act.

00:02:30.717 --> 00:02:34.888
We have to get that stolen
jewel back from him now.

00:02:34.922 --> 00:02:38.392
Damn thief! I'll capture
him for sure. You know?

00:02:38.425 --> 00:02:41.562
I say this Nezumi guy
is extremely clever.

00:02:41.595 --> 00:02:44.097
In all his thefts he's
never left any incriminating

00:02:44.131 --> 00:02:45.365
evidence behind.

00:02:45.399 --> 00:02:47.401
We shouldn't underestimate him.

00:02:47.434 --> 00:02:48.502
Yes, exactly.

00:02:48.535 --> 00:02:50.237
And that's why the
Leaf Police Force

00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:52.706
requested our assistance
in this matter.

00:02:52.739 --> 00:02:54.007
[Kotaro] Over there!

00:02:57.644 --> 00:02:58.645
Let's go!

00:03:01.782 --> 00:03:02.983
Stop!

00:03:09.923 --> 00:03:12.426
(men snoring)

00:03:13.493 --> 00:03:14.595
What's this?

00:03:22.569 --> 00:03:23.837
Where's Nezumi?

00:03:23.871 --> 00:03:26.106
I was sure we'd
cornered him this time.

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:28.909
He has to be one of these guys.

00:03:28.942 --> 00:03:30.777
Bring 'em all in.

00:03:30.811 --> 00:03:31.778
-Yes, sir!

00:03:31.812 --> 00:03:32.779
On it.

00:03:32.813 --> 00:03:34.181
[Man A] What's the big idea

00:03:34.214 --> 00:03:35.883
[Man B] Hey, lemme go!

00:03:35.916 --> 00:03:36.750
[Nezumi] What's the deal?

00:03:36.783 --> 00:03:37.918
We didn't do anything.

00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:39.753
Then I assume you'll
be happy to cooperate

00:03:39.786 --> 00:03:41.154
with our investigation.

00:03:41.188 --> 00:03:43.924
We believe that a jewel thief
has snuck into this group.

00:03:43.957 --> 00:03:45.025
A jewel thief?

00:03:45.058 --> 00:03:46.460
What are you talking about?

00:03:46.493 --> 00:03:47.794
I don't know anything.

00:03:47.828 --> 00:03:48.862
Once we've cleared you,

00:03:48.896 --> 00:03:50.797
you'll all be free to go.

00:03:50.831 --> 00:03:52.032
But before that happens,

00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.101
you'll have to be brought
in for questioning.

00:03:54.134 --> 00:03:55.369
Take 'em away.

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:56.837
-[Police A] Yes sir.
-[Police B] Yes sir.

00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:58.038
All right. On your feet.

00:03:58.071 --> 00:04:00.007
[Man B] I didn't do anything!

00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:01.441
[Police Man A] Calm down!

00:04:01.475 --> 00:04:02.442
All right, all right.

00:04:02.476 --> 00:04:04.044
-Quit pushing.
-This is harassment you know?

00:04:04.077 --> 00:04:06.046
Nezumi has to be one of those
guys...

00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:08.048
so I guess this means we can
say...

00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.550
"Mission accomplished," right?

00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:11.451
I guess so. Yeah.

00:04:11.485 --> 00:04:13.387
(cat meows)

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:15.889
(cat meows)

00:04:15.923 --> 00:04:18.926
(cat meowing)

00:04:18.959 --> 00:04:20.894
I wonder if this kitten got lost

00:04:20.928 --> 00:04:23.197
and separated from its mom.

00:04:23.230 --> 00:04:25.465
Man, it's such a
tiny little thing.

00:04:27.134 --> 00:04:30.404
(cat meowing)

00:04:30.437 --> 00:04:31.872
This is bad.

00:04:31.905 --> 00:04:33.240
Why?

00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:36.243
Because, we can't just leave
it out here all by itself.

00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:39.413
It seems lost and it
won't stop shaking.

00:04:39.446 --> 00:04:40.881
Poor little thing,

00:04:40.914 --> 00:04:43.984
but I can't have pets
at our house, so...

00:04:45.319 --> 00:04:47.354
What me?

00:04:47.387 --> 00:04:49.890
I don't really think I
can take it home tonight.

00:04:49.923 --> 00:04:53.560
I mean, I'd have to
ask my mom first.

00:04:53.594 --> 00:04:56.697
[Sarada] Well, if you can't
take it and I can't take it,

00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:59.867
then we're gonna have to
find somebody else who can.

00:04:59.900 --> 00:05:01.568
That means you, Mitsuki.

00:05:01.602 --> 00:05:04.037
You think you could take
this little guy home

00:05:04.071 --> 00:05:05.772
for the night please?

00:05:05.806 --> 00:05:07.074
Okay.

00:05:07.107 --> 00:05:08.275
(Sarada laughs)

00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:09.276
Great.

00:05:09.309 --> 00:05:10.077
Here.

00:05:10.110 --> 00:05:12.713
(Mitsuki sighs)

00:05:12.746 --> 00:05:15.082
(cat meows)

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:24.558
Hey, excuse me,

00:05:24.591 --> 00:05:27.628
but you really shouldn't
be mean to a kitten.

00:05:27.661 --> 00:05:29.196
Be mean?

00:05:29.229 --> 00:05:31.498
Is that cat you're
holding yours?

00:05:32.900 --> 00:05:34.034
Not really.

00:05:34.067 --> 00:05:35.736
I'm just taking
care of it tonight.

00:05:35.769 --> 00:05:37.738
Oh, I see.

00:05:37.771 --> 00:05:39.006
Well, even if that is the case,

00:05:39.039 --> 00:05:41.608
please try to be a little
bit gentler with him.

00:05:42.576 --> 00:05:44.011
No, I'm not saying
you can't hold a cat

00:05:44.044 --> 00:05:45.179
by the nape of its neck,

00:05:45.212 --> 00:05:46.413
at least for a while.

00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:49.049
But that kitten looks
very frightened to me.

00:05:49.082 --> 00:05:51.919
It's better to hold
them in your arms.

00:05:51.952 --> 00:05:55.022
(Mitsuki sighs)

00:05:59.793 --> 00:06:02.796
I wonder if Mitsuki's
gonna be okay.

00:06:02.829 --> 00:06:04.565
I'm sure he'll be fine.

00:06:04.598 --> 00:06:07.100
It's just that Mitsuki's
never really handled

00:06:07.134 --> 00:06:08.635
anything other than snakes.

00:06:08.669 --> 00:06:10.838
I think that maybe you
should have taken the kitten

00:06:10.871 --> 00:06:12.039
after all.

00:06:12.072 --> 00:06:14.675
Well, if I can just get
Himawari on my side,

00:06:14.708 --> 00:06:17.878
I'm pretty sure that my Mom
and Dad will say it's okay...

00:06:17.911 --> 00:06:20.180
but until I do that.

00:06:20.214 --> 00:06:22.749
I really hope that
Mitsuki's able to take care

00:06:22.783 --> 00:06:24.084
of that kitten by himself.

00:06:24.952 --> 00:06:26.720
You worry too much, you know
that?

00:06:47.474 --> 00:06:49.977
(cat meowing)

00:06:54.047 --> 00:06:56.750
(cat meowing)

00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:02.322
(Mitsuki exclaims)

00:07:19.806 --> 00:07:22.109
I wonder if it could
be feeling hungry.

00:07:28.815 --> 00:07:30.918
(cat meows)

00:07:30.951 --> 00:07:32.452
(cat meows)

00:07:32.486 --> 00:07:34.922
(cat meows)

00:07:34.955 --> 00:07:36.924
(cat meowing)

00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:38.559
